"'''The Love Club'''" is a song by New Zealand recording artist [[Lorde]], taken from her debut album ''[[The Love Club EP]]'' (2013). It was written by Lorde and [[Joel Little]], while production was handled by Little. Upon the release of the EP, the song was well received by music critics and peaked at number 17 on the [[New Zealand Singles Chart]]. Due to the chart performance in New Zealand, "The Love Club" was certified [[List of music recording certifications|gold]] by [[Recorded Music NZ]] for exceeding sales of 7,500 copies.

==Background and promotion==
{{Listen|filename=The Love Club Lorde.ogg|title="The Love Club"|description=A 19 second sample of the song|pos=left|format=[[Ogg]]}}
In 2012, ''[[The Love Club EP]]'' was made freely available on [[SoundCloud]].<ref>{{cite web| url= http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/legal-and-management/5819663/new-zealands-broods-signs-to-capitol-in-us-preps| title=New Zealand's Broods Signs To Capitol In U.S., Preps Debut Album with Lorde's Producer||first=Jason|last=Lipshutz| work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]| accessdate= 2014-01-05| date=2013-12-05}}</ref> Later in March 2013, the EP was released for [[music download|digital sales]] on [[iTunes Store]]s through [[Universal Music Group]].<ref name="EP">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/nz/album/the-love-club-ep/id614175625|title=The Love Club &ndash; EP by Lorde|publisher=[[iTunes Store]] |location=New Zealand|accessdate=2014-01-13}}</ref> The EP featured songs solely written by Lorde (credited under her birth-name Ella Yelich-O'Connor) and [[Joel Little]] and produced by Little, including "The Love Club".<ref name="Notes">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/the-love-club-mw0002512787|title=The Love Club &ndash; Lorde|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=2014-01-16}}</ref> To promote the EP, Lorde held a concert at [[(Le) Poisson Rouge|Le Poisson Rouge]] in New York and performed the song among other tracks from ''The Love Club EP'' on 6 August 2013, becoming her first US show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5638325/lorde-hypnotizes-at-first-us-show-live-review|title=Lorde Hypnotizes At First U.S. Show: Live Review|first=Jason|last=Lipshutz|work=Billboard|date=2013-08-07|accessdate=2014-01-16}}</ref> On 9 August 2013, Lorde performed "The Love Club" and "[[Royals (song)|Royals]]" on [[KCRW]] radio station.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7477555/lorde-gives-a-positively-regal-live-rendition-of-royals-at-kcrw-watch|title=Lorde Gives A Positively Regal Live Rendition Of 'Royals' At KCRW: Watch|first=Mike|last=Wass|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=2013-08-13|accessdate=2014-01-14}}</ref>

"The Love Club" is a [[pop music|pop]] song.<ref name="HuffPost"/> Lorde explained the song's lyrical meaning to ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine, "'The Love Club' is about an experience I had about a year ago where I met all these new friends and I fell in with them. It happened overnight and I couldn't think of anything but our friends and our situation. Then I started to maybe realize that group wasn't so good for me, and that my old friends and my family are the people I should be with. It's about being drawn into this crazy world, and you<U+2019>re all in love".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/thecut/2013/06/meet-lorde-the-teen-pop-star-with-no-selfies.html|title=Meet Lorde, the Teen Pop Star with a No Selfies Policy |work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|first=Kat|last=Stoffel|date=2013-06-29|accessdate=2014-05-27}}</ref>

==Reception==
Upon its release, "The Love Club" received mainly positive reviews from [[music journalism|music critics]]. Writing for ''[[The New Zealand Herald]]'', Chris Schulz wrote that the song was "the start of something very special indeed."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=10872495|title=Album review: Lorde, The Love Club EP|first=Chris|last=Schulz|work=[[New Zealand Herald]]|date=2013-03-21|accessdate=2014-01-13}}</ref> James Christopher Monger from [[AllMusic]] and ''[[The Nelson Mail]]'' writer Nick Ward picked it as one of the EP's standout tracks, alongside "[[Royals (song)|Royals]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/mw0002512787|title=Lorde: The Love Club EP &ndash; Overview|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|first=James|last=Christopher Monger|accessdate=2014-01-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/nelson-mail/entertainment/music/8791854/Lorde-The-Love-Club-EP|title=Lorde: The Love Club EP|work=[[The Nelson Mail]] |publisher=[[Fairfax New Zealand]] |first=Nick|last=Ward|date=2013-06-13|accessdate=2014-01-13}}</ref> Todd Luling from ''[[The Huffington Post]]'' labelled the song "a perfect pop song".<ref name="HuffPost"/> In New Zealand, the song peaked at number three on the [[New Zealand Artists Singles Chart]] on 25 March 2013,<ref name = "NZcharts">{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/nzsingles?chart=2158 |date=2013-03-25|title=Top 20 New Zealand Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|accessdate=2014-01-13}}</ref> and at number seventeen on the [[New Zealand Singles Chart]] on 10 June 2013.<ref name="NZChart"/> It was eventually certified Gold by [[Recorded Music NZ]] for sales of 7,500 copies there.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/nzsingles?chart=2277|title=Top 20 New Zealand Singles Chart|publisher=Recorded Music NZ|accessdate=2014-01-13}}</ref> In the United States, "The Love Club" peaked at number 18 on the [[Hot Rock Songs]] chart, published by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine.<ref name="Rock">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/1553855/lorde/chart?f=902|title=Lorde &ndash; Chart history: Rock Songs|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=2014-01-13}}</ref> The song was listed at number 60 on the 2013 year-end Hot Rock Songs chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/1553855/lorde/chart?f=1062|title=Lorde Album & Song Chart History|work=Billboard|accessdate=2014-01-28}}</ref>

"The Love Club" was included in the album ''Songs for the Philippines'', a charity album to support the people in the Philippines who suffered from [[Typhoon Haiyan]] (2013).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.3news.co.nz/Lorde-features-on-Typhoon-Haiyan-charity-album/tabid/418/articleID/322873/Default.aspx|title=Lorde features on Typhoon Haiyan charity album|publisher=[[3News]]|date=2013-11-26|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6Q7NSBnwu|archivedate=2014-06-06}}</ref>

